  The tiling is built strip by strip: Str(2), Str(3), ..., Str(n-1)
  Strip Str(k) has k-1 tiles
  Total tiles: 1 + 2 + ... + (n-2) = C(n-1, 2)
======================================================================

  n=5: Strips:
    Vertex 3 (strip Str(2)): 1 tiles = [(3, 1)]
    Vertex 4 (strip Str(3)): 2 tiles = [(4, 1), (4, 2)]
    Vertex 5 (strip Str(4)): 3 tiles = [(5, 1), (5, 2), (5, 3)]

